> I've managed to get out most of the rust out with a chain rolling around
> inside and some muratic acid and lots of hosing off.
> 
> In the other photos you can see that some of the black sludge that came out
> is actually viscous and runs: I let it sit overnight.  I imagine if there is
> any left it will just run down and block up the tubes at the bottom of the
> tank.
> 
> What's left now is this sludge layer you can see at the bottom.  The acid
> has turned the sludge yellowish from black but it's still hard to scrape.
> I'd appreciate any advice on removing this.
